python3 harness/trace.py success ...     # Record success trace
python3 harness/critic.py               # Analyze failure patterns
```

## Agent Work Rules

### Task Complexity
- Simple (one sentence, no "and"): do it directly
- Medium (multiple files, clear direction): create Team, delegate to Coder
- Complex (design decisions, trade-offs): Team + Coder (worktree) + Reviewer

### Coordinator Principles
- You are Team Lead — do NOT write business code for medium+ tasks
- Workflow: read docs → break down tasks → assign teammates → accept results → record traces
- Never "quickly fix this yourself" — delegate to a teammate

### Before Writing Code
- New file or cross-package import → run verify_action.py first
- Read docs/ARCHITECTURE.md layer rules before structural changes

### After Writing Code
- Run: python3 harness/validate.py
- Validation must pass before marking task complete

### Traces and Memory
- Task start: python3 harness/memory.py query "task keywords"
- Task success: python3 harness/trace.py success --task "..." --steps "..."
- Task failure: python3 harness/trace.py failure --task "..." --error "..."
- Long tasks: python3 harness/trace.py checkpoint after each stage

### Cross-Model Review
- Trigger: core business logic, security code, broad refactors
- python3 harness/review.py --diff "$(git diff)" --task "description"
  → assign output as Reviewer teammate task (model="codex")
